	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=2457">North Freeport</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>SOULFIRE You want it? You got it!</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    SOULFIRE You want it? You got it!</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=458596"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:gachamann@hotmail.com">Ravynn Solseer</a> | 
		                        6/29/2001 6:00:00 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">So we've all seen that fiery sword at one time or another and become extremely jealous. We've seen non-Pallys drool in awe at its sight as well. We know Soulfire doesn't stack up to other weapons like the Wurmslayer, but something about a fiery sword symbolizes everything we stand for as a Knight. Next time someone scoffs at a Soulfire and mentions a Wurmy, maybe also mentioning you can't use a shield, be sure to remind THEM that a wurmy doesn't give 5 complete heal charges. It also doesn't upgrade to a better weapon through a quest. And that upgrade, the Fiery Avenger, kicks the royal pants off a wurm. It also lets you bash, with a SWORD. And the stats on that sword more than make up for that shield they're taunting you about. That will shut them up real quick =)<BR>
<BR>
After all, that's what it's for. I can personally do without an FD, the quest is insanely hard. FA is hard as hell, but definitely doable, and something any knight worth his salt should strive for.<BR>
<BR>
But first you have to get the Soulfire, and that's why you're here. You can start the quest when you reach level 15 (and by all means you should), but it's very difficult to survive some parts of the quest when you're that low. It has been done, however, and if you've got enough friends to watch over you, you'll be set. So here we go, the complete and no-nonsense guide to getting your Soulfire. Heed it well!<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
STEP 1) Item collecting! Collect 5 of each: Rat ears, fire beetle eyes, and snake scales. These can all be had by killing at the commons, or buying off vendors. You will also need 1 spider venom sack. These come off desert tarantulas in Northern Ro, which is the opposite zone from the tunnel in EC. These can sometimes be extremely hard to come by. I killed desert tarantulas for 3 hours before one dropped. Check all vendors first and you may get lucky. I also recommend getting 2, which I will explain later.<BR>
<BR>
STEP 2) Create edible goo and bog juice from these items. Go to NFP and enter the inn next to Jade Tigers, next to the bank. Buy a bottle. You will see a brew kettle next to you. Place into the kettle the bottle, a snake scale, and a water flask. Press combine. This will create bog juice. If you fail just try again. You'll get your bottle back, and this is why I recommended getting 5 of each item. Once done, exit the inn and head straight across the street to the oven. Place into the oven a rate ear and a fire beetle eye. Press combine. This will make edible go. Again if you fail, just try until you succeed with the extra items on you. Once done, place in your pack, and be very careful that you have plenty of food and water so you don't accidentally eat/drink these items for sustenance.<BR>
<BR>
STEP 3) Go to the EFP docks and enter the tavern. Make sure you are in the big bar room with the 2 bar keeps. Buy 4-5 Drom's Champaignes. Your first wait for a spawn is upon you. Wait for Tykar Renklin to spawn (he looks like a desert madman). This can take hours, or he may be there as soon as you enter the room (I had to wait about 4 hours). As soon as he appears hail him to keep him from despawning. Continue hailing him, and while you do so give him 1 drom champaigne at a time. After 4-5 gives he will hand you a blanket.<BR>
<BR>
STEP 4) Go to the NFP Arena, and enter the first jail cell on your left. Hail the prisoner and he will ask you for some items. Give him the blanket, bog juice, and edible goo one at a time. He will hand you a key.<BR>
<BR>
STEP 5) Travel time! You didn't think the entire quest would take place in FPT did you? =) Run through EC and WC, past Kithicor Forest, through High Hold and into High Keep. Go to the bank there. Hail her and give her the key. She will hand you a &lt;Sealed Note&gt; to give to Brother Hayle.<BR>
<BR>
You now have the first item required for Soulfire, congratulations!<BR>
<BR>
STEP 6) Go back to EC and enter the Inn which lies between the two orc camps. Once inside, go to the vendor on the right and buy &quot;a cloth shirt&quot;. Run straight to the tunnel side of zone and enter a lone hut (no others around) which is near zone to WC. Wait for a man named Altunic Jartin to walk in. If he's not there it doesn't take long for him to show up, 5-10 min. max. Hand him the cloth shirt. He will give you a coin of generosity.<BR>
<BR>
STEP 7) Run to NFP. Enter the Hall of Truth area, and swim the right side of moat. Climb back onto firm ground on your left when you see the canoe. A man named Merko Quetalis (in all leather) will be standing there, below Valeron Dushire. Hail him and then hand him a Spider venom sack. He will reward you with a coin (you now have two). Hand BOTH coins back to him at the same time. As soon as you hand them in, IMMEDIATELY RUN your little hiney off and enter that sewer just behind you. A little tip. When trying to enter the sewer running, it's very easy to lose traction and slide past the entrance. I recommend you practice running into the sewers from Merko's location several times until you get a good feel for it. I say this for good reason. As soon as you enter the sewers, an exposed militia spy will appear immediately to your left in the corner. She will almost immediately try to run. If she does, she will zone through the sewers and escape. She is almost impossible to catch once she takes off, which is why you must practice the run I mentioned earlier. I missed the entrance from sliding, only delaying myself about 5 seconds. That was enough time for her to zip out of there, and I had to start this part all over again. This is also why I said to get more than one spider venom sack if it's available. It's a real pain to have to go back and start killing spiders again just to try this part of the quest again. If you have an extra, you only need to repeat the cloth shirt/Altunic coin portion before coming back.<BR>
<BR>
As soon as you see her, don't bother reading what she says, she's stalling for time. Attack! She's around level 12-15, so if you're not much above her, make sure you have a higher level friend to help keep her rooted and stunned. If you're in your high 20s+, you shouldn't have a problem. Again, attack/root/stun until she's down. Loot and you will receive another coin. Hand this over to Merko, and you will be rewarded with a &lt;Testament&gt;. Place this into the bank, as it is very easy to get it confused with the Lucan's Testament, and you don't want to get them mixed up and give Valeron the wrong one later, wasting your efforts. When you put the item into your bank, convert about 60-70pp to gold, and take it with you. Watch your encumbrance, as you have a long journey ahead of you.<BR>
<BR>
You now have your second item for Soulfire! You're on a roll now, halfway there already =)<BR>
<BR>
STEP 8) Now for the long journey. You knew there had to be at least one of these, didn't you? Zip over to Qeynos real quick. Ok, not so quick, but if you get a port to NKarana it will help immensely. Enter the Temple of Life area and you will see a Flying Saucer (very unique touch, we pallys get all the coolest stuff, hehe) for a temple. See that pond with all the cute little fish in there? Well dust off your Sgt Slaughter's hat on, because it's GO TIME! But not with your pally. You must raise your faction with the Temple to Allied. The quickest way is to loot the fish corpses here and hand them to the Knight who circles the pool. This will raise your faction extremely quickly. But it's a catch 22, because when you try to kill a fish (in order to loot), you will severely damage your faction, as they are holy fish to the temple. The Knight will also attack if he is anywhere near you when this happens.<BR>
<BR>
There are two methods. 1) Have a friend create a brand new warrior, put all his points into STR, and start him in Qeynos. He can then chop away at the fish, being careful of aggro range of the Knight, and you can loot the fish when looting rights to the warrior vanish. Do NOT help the warrior in any way once the fight commences, or your faction will also be damaged. Loot the fish when able, and turn them in to the Knight for Faction, and maybe an item or two. 2) If you have a fast connection, create your own warrior, kill the fish, camp out immediately, and come back in with your Pally and loot before the fish disappears. It can be done.<BR>
<BR>
This will take anywhere from 8 to 20 fish corpses, depending on your faction. If you are having a hard time, wait for Lashun Novashine to appear on the ramp leading to the saucer. Hail him and then give 2gp at a time for faction. This method is much slower, but is good when you're short on help for the fish. Also worth mention is the fish seem to disappear many time before you gain looting rights. I think Verant decided to &quot;modify&quot; the fish as it was &quot;too easy&quot; before (HAHA). So you will have times of frustration when the corpse simply vanishes. But this only happens some of the time, so be patient. Once allied status, you're done!<BR>
<BR>
STEP 9) Go back to WFP. Now the real fun begins. You are going to kill..let me rephrase..6 to 8 of your high level friends (40s+) are about to kill the evil and corrupt Sir Lucan, Captain of the Freeport Militia! He was once a Paladin who was corrupted by power, killing a fellow Knight and was stripped By Lord Marr of his powers, reduced to a lowly warrior. However he fights fiercely, dual-wielding and hitting for 100-150+. After your group is assembled at the west wall near zone to EC (you'll see a Cactus marker), have someone run in and pull him from the militia house out to the zone area. The puller and everyone else should zone except for one hailer who is not KOS. Have him hail Sir Lucan continuously so he does not return to the house. <BR>
<BR>
When all of the other guards (this may take a few minutes) go back into Freeport, have the attacking groups zone back in, and let the beatings begin. Regardless of where he is, Brother Jentry will run out and try to heal Lucan, so make sure someone watches for him, and then kites him to the other wall near zone line until Lucan is dead. <BR>
<BR>
Do NOT let your group ping-pong around the area, or the gate guards will aggro and join in the fight. Once Lucan dies his undead form will spawn into a weaker version. THIS corpse will give you his &lt;Testament&gt;. You may now finish off Brother Jentry. Anyone in group WILL become KOS when Lucan dies, so anyone who doesn't want the faction hit must zone before he goes down. You should stay in the zone. You're getting a lot of help, and many will become KOS in order to help you. Don't disgrace yourself by trying to save your own faction when they're doing this for you. Just stay in the zone, watch your group in case someone needs an LOC, and take lots of pics of the fight =)<BR>
<BR>
You now have 3 of the 4 items for Soulfire. One more to go!<BR>
<BR>
STEP 10!) Get another high-level group (mid 40s+) and head to Mistmoore. You are going to kill a 40 ShadowKnight by the name of Xicotl. He spawns in the SPA ROOM, and his Placeholder (PH) is a Mistmoore Guard. Camp the spa room and wait. We waited 4 hours the first time with no luck. The second time he popped after an hour, so be patient and expect that you may not get him the first time, depending on how long your party has to be there. The guards seem to spawn every 20-30 minutes, so don't get too excited when you see one, as you'll probably kill many before getting the actual PH. You need someone who knows MM fairly well, as it can be a very scary place if you don't know what you're doing. The mobs can be very high level (30s+), so watch yourself, and make sure you have a cleric or two (the available Rez may well come in handy). Once you've taken him down, grab the glowing hilt. <BR>
<BR>
STEP 11) Hand in Lucan's testament to Valeron Dushire, guild master of the Knights of Truth (if you didn't know that, you don't deserve the Soulfire, go pick another class LOL). Make sure he is allied first. If not, turn in slashed belts from orcs at camp 1 and 2 in EC to the Warrior Guildmaster in WFP. He is upstairs in the big room. Hand them in 2 at a time. If you're already KOS, seek out Celestion Vega (sp?). I'm probably way off on the spelling, but you will find the npc on the second or third floor in the temple of Marr, which is close to the Hall of Truth. Hail, ask about the fish, and you will receive a pouch with 4 slots. Kill the piranha in moat at Hall of Truth, and place their corpses into the pouch. When the 4 slots are filled, return to the Temple of Marr. Press combine on the pouch and hand it to the npc. You will gain faction with the Knights of Truth. Make sure you don't attack the minnow. This will hurt your faction, and the guards may attack you. The piranha spawn time is about 5 minutes. Rinse and repeat until Allied, then hand over the testament to Valeron. You will receive the Sword of Faith.<BR>
<BR>
You now have all 4 items for Soulfire!<BR>
1) Sealed Note for Brother Hayle<BR>
2) Testament from Merko<BR>
3) Sword of Faith<BR>
4) Glowing hilt<BR>
<BR>
STEP 11) Take a good level group (35+) to Splitpaw with you to retrieve the sword. Once you enter Splitpaw, you will likely need to fight through a few packs of gnolls, and they can be viscious so be careful. Find Brother Hayle's jail cell. Con him and make sure he is Allied. This is why you spent all that time in Qeynos, as their faction relates directly to his. Give him the sealed note. He will hand it back to you, unfolded. Now, hand the note back, along with the other 3 items (Testament, Sword of Faith, Glowing Hilt). <BR>
<BR>
*Trumpets blare rejoicefully and the Angels of Marr smile upon you*<BR>
<BR>
You have completed your quest honorably, and now wield Soulfire! Now go show it off to your friends ;)<BR>
<BR>
Don't stow it away for a better weapon, show it with pride! Only when you are bestowed the Fiery Avenger are you worthy of a better weapon, but that's another quest entirely....<BR>
<BR>
I hope this guide helps you immensely. If it does, I only ask in return that you check shops periodically for Spider venom sacks. Over time have a few in your bank. When you run across a younger Knight who has started his quest (and believe me you will), do your brothers a noble service and hand them one. They may never realize how much of a jump-start you're giving them, but you'll know from experience. I've been able to grab two since, and one is gone already, so they go quick!<BR>
<BR>
Happy hunting, and go show the world why we're so few...because the noble, the honorable, and the elite always are!<BR>
<BR>
- Ravynn Solseer<BR>
Knight of the 32nd Order<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

